projects.name: Applications for opticians
projects.description:
A series of systems that service several hundred Scandinavian opticians. The main product HORIZON is a hybrid desktop application with windows made in Delphi, .Net (WPF) as well as web views (CEF and Typescript Angular). Here I have worked on the following applications:

  • Web Booking (2019-2022): Appointment booking system for opticians' clients; for example. vision tests, etc. I have developed the application from scratch in Angular, and it is currently taken into use by approx. 200 stores in Denmark, Sweden and the Faroe Islands.
  • Web Admin (2020-2022): Account management page that manages user access, mobile user access, design, opening hours, preferred language, and several others in relation to customers' Web Booking. Also an application I have developed from scratch.
  • HORIZON (2020-22): Web windows developed in Angular for managing employees, agreement types, rehearsal rooms, appointment calendar, customers, suppliers, third-party payers, and frame and glass cards. Furthermore, I have handled language management on the project (XLIFF).
  • Web Share (2020-22): Repo with Npm packages that include styles, assets, components and other code shared between multiple web projects.
  • Storelist Editor (2020-2021): Small application for internal use in relation to creating, updating and synchronizing stores.
  • Cloud API (2021-2022): API for Authentication and settings for cloud apps. The API is hosted on Azure and ensures secure communication between the cloud and the stores' backend for frontend (BFF) in relation to e.g. appointments.
  • Microservices (2020-2022): A series of RESTful web services developed in ASP .NET Core for managing customers, agreements, inventory management, sales, vision tests and the like. I have worked on several of these services, as well as developed some of them from scratch.
  • HORIZON Mobile (2020-2022): Progressive Web App (PWA) developed in Angular for managing opticians' appointments. Here I have i.a. handled authentication with JSON Web Tokens (JWT).
